article.headline: Cornell 78, Keuka College 52
article.story: ITHACA, N.Y. (AP) -- Ryan Rourke scored 22 points and grabbed 14 rebounds to lead Cornell to a 78-52 win over Division III Keuka Friday night. Ugo Ihekweazu added 10 points for the Big Red (5-8), who shot 74 percent from the floor in the second half to snap a two-game losing streak. Cornell opened the second half with a 14-0 run to build on a 33-28 halftime lead. The Big Red forced 23 turnovers and outrebounded the Storm 36-27. Keuka (5-2) shot 50 percent in the first half but only 37.5 percent after the break. Todd Lincoln led the Storm with 17 points, while Corey Edwards had 10.
